  "prompt": "I never write lyrics before, how to write song lyrics?",
  "response": "Writing song lyrics can be a highly personal and creative process. Here are some steps to help you get started:\n\n### 1. Find Inspiration\n- **Personal experiences:** Your own feelings, experiences, and thoughts are often the best source of inspiration.\n- **Stories:** Think about stories you've read or heard that resonated with you.\n- **Emotions:** Consider the emotions you want to convey to your audience.\n\n### 2. Choose a Topic or Theme\n- **Reflection:** What message do you want to share? Is it about love, loss, happiness, or any other topic?\n- **Clarity:** Try to be clear about the theme of your song to make it cohesive and focused.\n\n### 3. Understand Song Structure\n- **Verse:** Sets up the story or theme.\n- **Chorus:** The repeated, catchy part of the song that emphasizes the main message.\n- **Bridge:** Provides a contrast, often leading back into the final chorus.\n- **Intro/Outro:** Sets the mood and provides closure.\n\n### 4. Write the Lyrics\n- **Start with a hook:** A catchy phrase or line that captures the essence of the song.\n- **Build around the hook:** Develop verses and a chorus that revolve around your hook.\n- **Be relatable:** Use language and narratives that your audience can connect with.\n- **Use imagery:** Convey emotions and settings through vivid imagery.\n\n### 5. Edit and Revise\n- **Consider flow:** Ensure the lyrics fit well with the melody and rhythm.\n- **Refine:** Check for any awkward phrasing or anything that doesn\u2019t fit.\n- **Feedback:** Share your lyrics with friends or fellow musicians for input.\n\n### 6. Combine with Music\n- **Collaboration:** Work with composers or musicians to set your lyrics to music.\n- **Experiment:** Try different melodies, chords, and arrangements to find the best fit.\n\n### Tips for Improvement\n- **Listen:** Pay attention to songs you love and analyze their structure and language.\n- **Practice:** Like any skill, writing improves with practice.\n- **Stay Persistent:** Don\u2019t get discouraged if your early attempts don\u2019t meet your expectations. Keep writing.\n\nRemember, there is no single right way to write song lyrics. It's an art form, and your unique voice and perspective are valuable.",
